commentTextItems.html: full toss scooped high in the air on the leg-side but it carries over the in-field and they come back for the all important second. Victory to Canada

commentPostTextItems.html: Well that's it. What a great run chase from Canada after Scotland set them an ambitious target of 287 for victory. After centuries from Watts and Hamilton it looked like the Canadians wouldn't have a chance but the visitors came out fighting and matched
Scotland blow-for-blow all the way eventually passing the finishing line with 8 balls to spare

The Scottish team look dejected and head off for a warm-down job while the Canadian team are partying in the dressing room and have Jyoti who hit 117 and their skipper Bagai on 92* to thank for their efforts.
Do join us at the same time here tomorrow where the teams do it all over again in the second ODI where the Scots will look for revenge while the Canadians will want to take the series 2-0.
Thanks for joining us here on cricinfo but for now it's goodbye from me Callum Stewart. See you tomorrow for the second ODI between Scotland and Canada and that other game.

commentTextItems.html: yorker ball dug out towards point and they scramble a single
goes for the big shot but the ball just rolls down the wicket back to Drummond
turned straight at midwicket
fuller length ball dug out to the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: Only three runs needed for victory

DF Watts 100 in 149 mins off 105 balls, hitting 6 fours and 2 sixes.

milestones.description: Ashish Bagai and Sandeep Jyoti's 146-run partnership is CAN's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 100 between Ashish Bagai and Ashif Mulla
Hamilton and Fraser Watts's 203-run partnership is SCOT's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 103 between Fraser Watts and Majid Haq
Hamilton and Fraser Watts's 203-run partnership is SCOT's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 122 between Colin Smith and Hamilton

stories.title: Jyoti and Bagai steer Canada to victory
stories.subTitle: Scotland v Canada, 1st ODI, Aberdeen
stories.summary: Gavin Hamilton and Fraser Watts scored hundreds for the hosts but their efforts were overshadowed by Canada's centurion, Sandeep Jyoti, and Ashish Bagai who pulled off the chase with eight balls to spare
